Description: fix out-of-bounds write in FFI VLA buffers (GC64 segfault)
 same fix than cratered
 Here is the explanation that Claude Sonnet 4.6 wrote about the fix :
 Fix: change glIntv(0) to glIntv(1) (and equivalents) in all affected files
 so that each "output pointer" buffer has room for the one value GL writes.
Author: Nicolas HOUDELOT <nicolas@demosdebs.org>
Applied-Upstream: no
Last-Update: 2026-04-22
---
This patch header follows DEP-3: http://dep.debian.net/deps/dep3/
